## Challenge 3 - Printing Quotes

### Goal
Create a program that prompts for a quote and an author. Display the quotation and author as shown in the example output

### Inputs
quoteString
authorName

### Outputs
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for quoteString with "What is the quote?"
Prompt for authorName with "Who said it?"

Contatenate finalMessage with "authorName says, "quoteString."" (using escape characters)

Display finalMessage

### JS
```
function quoteAuthor(quoteString) {
    var authorName = prompt("Who said it?");
    if (authorName) {
        var finalMessage = authorName + ' says, \"' + quoteString + '.\"';
        alert (finalMessage);    
    } else {
        alert("Sorry I didn't catch that. If the author is unknown, write just that or \"annonymous!\"");
        quoteAuthor(quoteString);
    }
}
function printingQuotes() {
    var quoteString = prompt("What is the quote?");
    if (quoteString) {
        quoteAuthor(quoteString);
    } else {
        alert("Quotes require words! Please input the quote.");
        printingQuotes();
    }
}
```

