## Challenge 5 - Simple Math

### Goal
Write a program that prompts for two numbers. Print the sum, difference, product, and quotient of those numbers as shown in the example output

### Inputs
firstNum
secondNum

### Outputs
sumEquation
differenceEquation
productEquation
quotientEquation

### Pseudocode
Prompt for firstNum with "What is the first number?"
Prompt for secondNum with "What is the second number?"

Convert firstNum to number format
Convert secondNum to number format

Concatenate sumEquation with firstNum "+" secondNum "=" (firstNum + secondNum)
Concatenate differenceEquation with firstNum "-" secondNum "=" (firstNum - secondNum)
Concatenate productEquation with firstNum "*" secondNum "=" (firstNum * secondNum)
Concatenate quotientEquation with firstNum "/" secondNum "=" (firstNum / secondNum) and rounding to the nearest hundredth

Display sumEquation, differenceEquation, productEquation, and quotientEquation altogether with line breaks

### JS
```
function num1Input () {
    var num1 = prompt("What is the first number? (default: 0)");

    if (!isNaN(num1)) {
        num1 = Number(num1);
        return num1;
    } else {
        alert("I need a first number, please!");
        num1Input();
    }
}

function num2Input () {
    var num2 = prompt("What is the second number? (default: 0)");

    if (!isNaN(num2)) {
        num2 = Number(num2);
        return num2;
    } else {
        alert("I need a second number, please!");
        num2Input();
    }
}

function simpleMath() {
    var num1 = num1Input();
    var num2 = num2Input();

    numSum = parseFloat(num1 + num2).toFixed(2);
    numDifference = parseFloat(num1 - num2).toFixed(2);
    numProduct = parseFloat(num1 * num2).toFixed(2);
    numQuotient = parseFloat(num1 / num2).toFixed(2);

    var sumEquation = `${num1} + ${num2} = ${numSum}`;
    var differenceEquation = `${num1} - ${num2} = ${numDifference}`;
    var productEquation = `${num1} * ${num2} = ${numProduct}`;
    var quotientEquation = `${num1} / ${num2} = ${numQuotient}`;

    alert(`${sumEquation} \n ${differenceEquation} \n ${productEquation} \n ${quotientEquation}`);
}
```


