## Challenge 6 - Retirement Calculator

### Goal
Create a program that determines how many years you have left until retirement and the year you can retire. It should prompt for your current age and the age you want to retire and display the output

### Inputs
currentAge
retireAgeGoal

### Outputs
yearsLeft
retireYear
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for currentAge with "What is your current age?"
Prompt for retireAgeGoal with "At what age would you like to retire?"

Convert currentAge to number format
convert retireAgeGoal to number format

Calculate yearsLeft with retireAgeGoal - currentAge
Calculate retireYear with currentYear (built-in function) + yearsLeft

Concatenate finalMessage with "You have yearsLeft years left until you can retire. It's currentYear, so you can retire in retireYear." with line break between sentences.

Display finalmessage

### JS
```
function inputCurrentAge () {
    var currentAge = prompt("What is your current age?");

    if (!isNaN(currentAge) && (currentAge != "")) {
        currentAge = Number(currentAge);
        return currentAge;
    } else {
        alert("Don't be shy! I won't tell!");
        inputCurrentAge();
    }
}

function inputRetireAgeGoal () {
    var retireAgeGoal = prompt("At what age would you like to retire?");

    if (!isNaN(retireAgeGoal) && (retireAgeGoal != "")) {
        retireAgeGoal = Number(retireAgeGoal);
        return retireAgeGoal;
    } else {
        alert("I didn't catch that!");
        inputRetireAgeGoal();
    }
}

function retirementCalculator() {
    var currentAge = inputCurrentAge();
    var retireAgeGoal = inputRetireAgeGoal();

    var yearsLeft = retireAgeGoal - currentAge;
    var currentYear = Number(new Date().getFullYear());
    var retireYear = currentYear + yearsLeft;
    var finalMessage = (`You have ${yearsLeft} years left until you can retire.\nIt's ${currentYear}, so you can retire in ${retireYear}.`);

    alert(finalMessage);
}
```


